What a amazing vibe!  The Wunder Garten has manage to hold onto some kind of normalcy during a pandemic which is great to see.  The inside feels like stepping into Colorado, which is what they are trying to inspire with their Colorado ski resort named hutches.  The little tables have fire in the center to keep patrons warm.  There is a large inside tented area which is warmer and also has great music blasting the whole time.  The bathrooms are a trailer, but are clean and adequate.  Overall, fabulous time!  Great beers in big glasses, and great online ordering system.  A+, Wunder Garten!

Covid-19 Review: First time visiting and there was both an indoor and outdoor area.  I walked in and it felt like I was in college at a keg party freezing my butt off.  This was their aprés ski event with spiked hot chocolate.  What to expect: -Chaos -Heat lamps with propane tanks dying and not emitting any heat -ZERO Covid friendly measures: absolutely no clean up after people leave, I never saw anyone wipe down a table and chairs, no hand sanitizer on any of the tables, people just left their trash everywhere -Drinks were very expensive for spiked hot chocolate $15-$16 and barely tasted any booze -If you sit outside and are hoping to get inside there is no organized method to facilitate that -Social distancing not enforced especially indoors -Our spiked hot chocolate drinks were good but we couldn't stay for more than one just due to the unsafe environment and no warmth to be found -Lots of dogs so very pet friendly -There are cabins you can reserve and rent for $$$$ which are enclosed with couches and heat  I’d suggest bringing your own blanket if you plan on being outdoors, it was quite windy and since the setup is like a fort it feels like a wind tunnel.
It was safe as can be. Though it was practically empty. A qr code on the table to order drinks by phone. We had one and left

Don't sit in the beer garden style tables, I'm never coming here with my dog again. The way the staff explained it afterwards is that the tables are apparently designed to work like seesaws, however none of this was ever clear when I sat at the edge of the bench, causing the bench to topple over. I fell, the bench fell, and it landed on my dog's left hind leg. The vet said his leg is fractured and may permanently have a limp. They said they probably won't change the tables' design because of the aesthetic, which is the worst excuse you can give when a good portion of this place isn't even the beer garden style tables.

I loved Wundergarten pre-COVID, but after coming here for the first time since reopening I do not feel comfortable coming back. Once inside everything feels fine and the atmosphere is still fun, but the bouncer outside really ruined the night for me. He was incredibly rude and kept directing us to one side of the gate, which was much closer to him that 6 feet. He then said “did you all not hear me?” When I stayed where I was, 6 feet across from him. We were not blocking the sidewalk (only two of us)and were the only ones in line. He then demanded to hold our ids (I promptly wiped with sanitizer) and his request for us to remove our masks and then the way he dictated the rules was demeaning. It gave off a very negative vibe for the rest of the evening. I’m sure he deals with a lot of people not following the rules, and these are definitely uncertain times so I’m certainly more lenient for frustration. However, for this to be the first contact with Wundergarten, I found it unacceptable from a customer service and experience standpoint.

Yelp Write a Review  Austin G. Wunder Garten At Noma Read our review guidelines  A-OK.  All changes saved  Wunder Garten is a large beer garden in the heart of NoMa, close to the Metro. We went during the holidays for their Winterfest. A few things to note:  1) Space: It's pretty big. There are several sections with bars and picnic-style seating outside and two indoor rooms with their own bars.  2) Atmosphere: During the holidays, they have an igloo, Christmas trees for sale, and a room decorated like Christmas.  3) Drinks: They have a large menu.  If you're looking for a good space to hang out with a large group, look no further.

It's a really nice outdoor bar with lots of games to play AND dogs are welcome. I wouldn't go there during the summer without spraying bug spray first tho.

I used to live in Germany, not that this constitutes as anything near a German experience, but overall I find the options for beer nostalgic of my time there. The gardens themselves and seating areas are lush and inviting, making each turn more difficult from the last in terms of making a decision. They have yard games that most are playing with in the evening like Giant Jenga. The only thing that's slightly disappointing is the food truck that looms in the back as their only food option. However, I'm grateful there is food available and bathrooms behind the center tent (where you purchase drinks and watch soccer games). I remember visiting during the World Cup and seeing some guy get thrown out in front of us so note that if there are sour apples in the crowd, security is quick! haha This space is perfect for groups, dog friendly, and great for large events. Very strict ID check in so make sure you have your driver's license on ya!
Blues Festival held in Wunder Garten. Not perfect but good venue. Overall love the ambience and setting.
The DJ was awesome, she took us down memory lane. She is great,

Nice outdoor beer garden. Mostly German beer selection. Picnic tables for seating. Opens at 4 during the week. Oddly (for me) lots of kids running around. It seems to be tolerated. It appears to be a popular local hangout.

One of the best beer selections in DC and they are very knowledgeable. It's a shame you can't get decent snacks without going to a food truck, though. No big kitchen or anything, just something to keep you going. Otherwise, great!
Bustling outdoor bar with a good clientele. Decent beer selection, and we had the caliburger food truck which was just excellent!

Wunder Garten is my favorite beer garden in DC and one of my favorite place to just hang on a Sunday afternoon. Unlike most beer gardens, Wunder Garten really utilizes its space to create what I call a backyard made for family and friends get together.  Their incorporation of games, cabanas, and live music make for a warm, intimate relaxing vibe that you can really kick back and enjoy a beer.  You can also get simple and filling eats to enjoy.  And if it happens to rain, the fun continues because of their large enclosed space. Their staff are also great. They are friendly and informed about the beer selections. Wunder Garten is also LGBTQ approved as they are welcoming to the gay community and people from diverse cultures.  Plus they are also dog friendly. :-)
Really chill place to go after work when the weather is nice. Fair prices, music can be a little unnecessarily loud, but great atmosphere as a whole.
Great place to hang out and drink beer.
Fun space with games for adults and room to let kids play. Nice beer options plus food trucks.
Friendly staff. Comfortable atmosphere.
It was nice for a party.
A Chic little spot with a great burger food truck
Excellent beer selection! Good German beers.

Cool idea, lots of flowers and grass akd places to sit. They even have a tent area with TVs. The beer selection is good. However, on hot days, there us no where outside tent to sit with access to a fan. Not a good place for hot days.

Beer garden near NoMa metro. Great spot bc there aren't many options in this area for happy hour, etc. Food trucks and many beer taps. So defintiely serves it's purpose.  Decent selection of beer. Friendly staff. The location is weather dependent. No A/C. The bugs are bad at times too.
Mainly outdoors. Large and very nice
Fun Saturday afternoon destination!!🍺🍺
Nice setting with friendly faces and various games to play and watch on their tvs. Drink prices are too high for only 4oz with mainly juice mixed. Food selection is limited and parking is limited.
Nice outdoor popup bar. Decent but small beer selection
Very nice and open space. Good place if you have kids.
I LOVE THIS PLACE !
Big beer garden with games. It’s also a good place to catch a game on TV
It's a very diverse, outdoor ambiance with a decent selection of beers. It's easy to get lost in the numerous niche seating areas.
Great atmosphere! It's what I would compare to hanging out with friends in our backyard. Good selection of beer and wonderful staff!! Definitely one of my top favorite places in DC!
They have a giant chess board!! Neat little place. We went after it rained (outdoor bar) and it was still awesome! Cool atmosphere
Nice atmosphere, good beer list, and it's even open in the winter which is cool.
Best beer garden in town!
Nice open air beer garden, dog friendly, good spot to watch a game or just relax with friends.
The perfect place to watch the world cup...even if Germany didn't make it past the groups 😔
Not a huge beer selection but it's a really nice atmosphere and alot of space to sit and stand

One of the most fun and unique spots in DC - I love the open garden area and funky decor. Really awesome spot to check out after work, for Sunday Funday or to catch a game on TV. Wish they served food (food truck on-site is way overpriced and the food subpar in my opinion) but I'm reviewing them, not the food truck :).
Cool spot with some great beer. Usually a food truck or two on site if you're looking for more than drinks.
Fun place to watch world cup
Oh my gosh this place!

This place is funky and fun. It is very casual and there are always dogs, babies, and various parties hanging out. The unique set up and varied seating makes it fun every time. The accompanying food trucks are hit or miss.
Great drinks and fun food options. It's all outside, so if you're here in the middle of a summer afternoon you will probably be sweating.
Great beer and world cup matches.
Ok. Plastic cups takes away some of the charm. And it is kind of loud.
Great place to hang and have a beer.
Good atmosphere, selection, and vibe.  Great way to spend happy hour or meetup with friends.

Cool place to grab a few drinks. Have lawn games, like corn hole and chess. Wednesday night is trivia night, it is not insanely difficult. Which makes it fun for everyone who wants to participate. Happy hour is at the cheapest but the beer and cocktails are good. The staff was very knowledgeable and friendly as well. Dog friendly
This place is awesome and I might have hallucinated it. It seems less North Capitol than Berlin. So good. Very casual. Play time.

Great atmosphere (mostly outside seating and some inside) tables are large so ideal for a large after work gathering, limited drinking and eating options though

Definitely the best beer garden I've been to. The service is quick and efficient, the vibe is chill, there's lot's of room. I've never gone when it was super crowded, but when I've gone it's been a great place to be.
Love love love. Great concept, great staff, great atmosphere. Really nicely executed.

Well set up, good job on the staging and bathroom trailers

Everyone standing in the picture is in some sort of beer line. I have no plans to come back here. Staff up to meet your demand or just don't let this many people in.

I live in NE, and I really enjoy Wunder Garten. It's kinda like a cheap theme park for adults who want cocktails, and unhealthy food. It's great in the summer when it's hot and you can have a cold beer outside. And it's nice in the winter when they tent off the warm parts and serve shamefully good food (I don't think they have hot beverages though).  Only sucky thing is they aren't open everyday (check the hours, but they're closed Sun-Tues in the winter).
Great place for date night!

Excellent place to go and just chill for a while. The outside area looks amazing. Although, I did go in the winter season, but they have a great covered hall with heaters and airflow. Had an amazing time. Also the people there know the drinks and give good recommendations.

Wunder Garten is a fun, lively beer garten in NE. Don't be deterred by the outside, it's truly a wonderland on the other side of the fence (or wonder garden, if you catch my drift). Bonus-- it's dog friendly! Who doesn't love sipping some beers and petting some cute pups?! They have several tables acceptable for large groups and lawn games, as well as covered space for colder days.
Meh. It's okay. A little underwhelming.
